Sunny- little wind.  Very bad algae bloom- started mid July.

Sunny- light wind.  Algae still very bad.  1 goose- 2 ducks on lake.  This season:  Every time I was out I looked for weed growth and didn't see any weeds.  There were some weeds at the first part of the spring- but by mid summer- they were all gone.  The water quality really went bad about the time of year that the weeds were gone.
mostly sunny- little wind- training with debra today
sunny- mild wind- lots of green algae
very bad algae bloom- rained 7-23-05- light wind
algae still present- rained on 8-11-05- sunny- light wind
sunny mild wind- water not as green- rained on 9-13-05
nice day- little wind- water looks good

mild wind- mostly cloudy- water looks very good- still
mild wind- mostly cloudy- water looks good.
sunny water looks really good for this time of year- light wind

Mild wind.  Water looks really good.
Plenty of blue-green algae present.  Cloudy with light wind.  No rain since July 5th.
Partly cloudy.  Wind out of the north.  Lot of rain the last 2 weeks.
Light Wind- Sunny- Water looks good
Light Wind- Sunny. Water looks good Light Wind-Sunny-Water looks good

A lot of algae around the perimeter.
Lake level 1 1/2' below normal; very little algae present.
The lake had alot of rain and snow in April. Air temp. was below for April.  Batteries died so was unable to get complete D.O. info.
water is clearest we've seen it since carp removal.
Water is full of algae = grass clipping variety of algae
Very litlle "grass clipping" algae- secchi depth is unbelievable! Highest Ever!!!
grass algae is very abundant. Weed growth is increasing dramatically!!
There are several nice cattails stands established around the lake.
grass algae is greatly reduced- surface green "scum"
No algae observed - normal this time of year.  Lake looks good!
Water very green.  Lake has strong algae levels.
Water very green- didn't see "grass clipping" algae.
Water very green- very little rain in area for weeks.
Very green water.  No grass clipping algae.  Dense weed growth along shore.
Very green- green "scum" along shore line has decreased.  No "grass clipping" present.
Green "scum" has dissipated- water is not good.
Water is relatively clear- slight green tint.  No "grass clipping" algae noticed.
blue-green algae beginning around perimeter; grass algae was not evident
blue-green algae increasing in area and quantity; water is brownish tint; grass algae not present
blue-green algae is very thick on entire lake surface
Lake water is muddy brown with green algae along the shoreline
Water very green- no blue green algae observed

no algae apparent at this time
